    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-25T11:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-25T11:54:00-05:00" n="940"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d940">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-25T20:00:00+03:06"
                            >August 25, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 26—7:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Department’s 52, August 17, midnight.<note n="90" xml:id="d940fn90">See
                        telegram No. 1172 to the Minister in Egypt, <ref target="#pg_891">p.
                            891</ref>.</note> I see no way in which suggested procedure could be
                    improved upon. It is requested that this Legation be supplied with copies of any
                    requests, reports or recommendations relative to silver for Saudi Arabia not
                    submitted from here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
